---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-coverage', text: 'Plans and Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pros-and-cons', text: 'Pros and Cons', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-and-service', text: 'Claims and Service', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who It\'s For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'Alternatives to Consider', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'BUPA in the UK', href: '/countries/uk/insurance/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'BUPA in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'BUPA in Thailand', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance/bupa-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage Level' },
  { key: 'maternity', header: 'Maternity' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Major Medical', coverage: 'Emergencies only', maternity: 'No', bestFor: 'Catastrophic coverage' },
  { plan: 'Select', coverage: 'Basic regional', maternity: 'No', bestFor: 'Budget-conscious' },
  { plan: 'Premier', coverage: 'Comprehensive', maternity: 'Add-on', bestFor: 'Most expats' },
  { plan: 'Elite', coverage: 'Premium', maternity: 'Included', bestFor: 'Full protection' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="BUPA Global Review"
  description="In-depth review of BUPA Global international health insurance. Coverage options, pricing, pros and cons for expats."
  headline="BUPA Global International Health Insurance Review"
  subheadline="A detailed look at BUPA Global's plans, pricing, and whether they might be right for your expat needs."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a BUPA Global Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global is the international arm of Bupa, a healthcare company with over 75 years of history. Unlike most insurers, Bupa has no shareholders—they reinvest profits back into healthcare services. This structure has helped them build a reputation for quality coverage and customer care.
  </p>
  <p>
    With a presence in over 190 countries and a network of 1.7 million healthcare providers, BUPA Global is one of the premium options in the international health insurance market. They're particularly well-regarded for comprehensive coverage and strong customer service.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Quick Facts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>Headquarters:</strong> London, UK</li>
      <li><strong>Founded:</strong> 1947 (75+ years)</li>
      <li><strong>Network Providers:</strong> 1.7 million+</li>
      <li><strong>Countries Covered:</strong> 190+</li>
      <li><strong>Plan Types:</strong> Major Medical, Select, Premier, Elite</li>
      <li><strong>Age Limit:</strong> Up to 74 to enroll</li>
      <li><strong>Trustpilot Rating:</strong> 4.4/5 stars</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Personalized Quote"
    description="See what BUPA Global would cost for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="plans-and-coverage">Plans and Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global offers four plan tiers, from basic catastrophic coverage to comprehensive premium protection. Each tier offers different levels of benefits and pricing.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Major Medical</h3>
  <p>
    The most affordable option, designed for catastrophic coverage only. It covers emergencies, major medical expenses, and evacuation but has a high deductible (around $6,300/£5,000) and doesn't cover routine care, wellness visits, or maternity.
  </p>

  <h3>Select</h3>
  <p>
    Basic coverage with regional (rather than worldwide) options. Covers health screenings and wellness after a 10-month waiting period, but excludes maternity, dental, and optical.
  </p>

  <h3>Premier</h3>
  <p>
    Comprehensive coverage suitable for most expats. Includes health screenings, vaccinations, dental, and optical. Maternity available as an add-on. Covers medical evacuation but not repatriation.
  </p>

  <h3>Elite</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global's most comprehensive plan. Includes everything in Premier plus:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine maternity care (after waiting period)</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li>Complementary therapies</li>
    <li>Enhanced wellness benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Standout Features</h3>

  <h4>Mental Health Parity</h4>
  <p>
    BUPA Global treats mental health equally to physical health. Both annual and monetary limits for inpatient and day-patient mental health treatment match physical health coverage. They also cover ADHD, addiction treatment, and self-inflicted injuries—benefits often excluded by competitors.
  </p>

  <h4>Pre-Existing Conditions</h4>
  <p>
    BUPA Global takes a more favorable approach to pre-existing conditions than many competitors. Many conditions may be covered, subject to underwriting. Your health history is assessed individually rather than applying blanket exclusions.
  </p>

  <h4>Digital Services</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Global Virtual Care:</strong> 24/7 telemedicine through the MembersWorld app</li>
    <li><strong>Second Medical Opinion:</strong> Expert review for serious, complex, or chronic conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Claims via app:</strong> Submit and track claims digitally</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Waiting Periods</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accidental dental:</strong> Immediate</li>
    <li><strong>Routine dental:</strong> 6 months</li>
    <li><strong>Wellness checks:</strong> 10 months</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> 18 months</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global is positioned as a premium provider, so expect higher prices than budget alternatives. However, their coverage quality and customer service often justify the cost.
  </p>

  <h3>Estimated Monthly Premiums (Worldwide excluding USA)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 30, Premier plan: $200-350/month</li>
    <li>Age 40, Premier plan: $300-450/month</li>
    <li>Age 50, Premier plan: $400-600/month</li>
    <li>Age 60, Premier plan: $550-800/month</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <em>Estimates vary significantly based on coverage area, deductible, and add-ons. Major Medical plans cost considerably less; Elite plans cost more.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Ways to Reduce Premiums</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductible:</strong> Major Medical's high deductible keeps premiums low</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Select Europe or specific regions instead of worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Exclude US coverage:</strong> Significant savings if you won't visit the US</li>
    <li><strong>No-claims discount:</strong> BUPA offers discounts for claim-free years</li>
    <li><strong>Professional discounts:</strong> Doctors and dentists get 15% off</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="See Your Actual Price"
    description="Get a quote based on your age, location, and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Excellent customer reviews (4.4/5 Trustpilot)</li>
        <li>Mental health covered equally to physical</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions often covered</li>
        <li>Large global network (1.7M+ providers)</li>
        <li>24/7 multilingual support team</li>
        <li>Strong telemedicine and digital tools</li>
        <li>Second Medical Opinion service included</li>
        <li>No-claims discounts available</li>
        <li>75+ years of healthcare experience</li>
        <li>No shareholders (reinvests in healthcare)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
        <li>Premium pricing (not budget-friendly)</li>
        <li>Long maternity waiting period (18 months)</li>
        <li>Some admin/onboarding issues reported</li>
        <li>Benefit levels vary by country</li>
        <li>Not the cheapest option available</li>
        <li>Some waiting periods for routine benefits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="claims-and-service">Claims and Service</h2>

  <h3>Filing Claims</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global offers multiple ways to file claims:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>MembersWorld mobile app</li>
    <li>Online portal</li>
    <li>Direct settlement with network providers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Customer reviews frequently praise their claims processing. One reviewer noted: "All the claims are settled timely and have hardly any claim rejected in past 4 years." The company reports efficient turnaround times for most claims.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global provides 24/7 support through a team of advisers, doctors, and nurses based around the world. They offer:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Multilingual support</li>
    <li>Medical advice hotline</li>
    <li>Treatment pre-authorization</li>
    <li>Emergency evacuation coordination</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Their 4.4/5 Trustpilot rating reflects generally positive customer experiences, though some reviews mention occasional administrative delays during onboarding.
  </p>

  <h3>Pre-Existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global's approach to pre-existing conditions is more flexible than many competitors. They assess each applicant individually and may cover conditions that other insurers exclude. However, coverage is subject to underwriting, and some conditions may still be excluded or have waiting periods.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who It's For</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global may be a good fit if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Want premium coverage with excellent service</li>
    <li>Value mental health coverage parity</li>
    <li>Have pre-existing conditions and want a fair assessment</li>
    <li>Appreciate strong digital tools and telemedicine</li>
    <li>Can afford higher premiums for quality coverage</li>
    <li>Want a provider with a long, stable history</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    It may not be ideal if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
    <li>Need maternity coverage soon (18-month wait)</li>
    <li>Want the absolute lowest premiums available</li>
    <li>Prefer newer, more agile insurance providers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Consider</h2>
  <p>
    If BUPA Global doesn't seem like the right fit, consider these alternatives:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Similar quality, slightly lower prices, excellent network. <a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> More flexible deductibles, competitive pricing. <a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly option with solid coverage. <a href="/providers/img-global">Read our review</a></li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Compare?"
    description="See how BUPA Global compares to other options for your needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This review is for informational purposes only. Plan details, pricing, and availability change frequently. We are not affiliated with BUPA Global and are not insurance brokers. Verify all information directly with BUPA Global before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
